n/core-api/src/core_api/services/doc_indexing.py:\n  Line 10: - The only embeddable field is ``data[\"summary\"]``.\n\n  Line 13:   without a migration. Server prefers ``summary`` when both are\n\n  Line 17: - All other collections may omit a summary; the doc is then stored\n\n  Line 36:             a skills write with neither ``summary`` nor ``description``,\n\n  Line 37:             or a non-skills write that provides ``summary`` but with a\n\n  Line 40:     summary = data.get(\"summary\")\n\n  Line 41:     summary_ok = isinstance(summary, str) and summary.strip()\n\n  Line 44:         if summary_ok:\n\n  Line 45:             return summary\n\n  Line 50:             \"collection='skills' requires data['summary'] (preferred) or \"\n\n  Line 54:     if summary is None:\n\n  Line 56:     if not summary_ok:\n\n  Line 57:         raise InvalidDocIndexingError(\"data['summary'], when present, must be a non-empty string.\")\n\n  Line 58:     return summary\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/suppression.py:\n  Line 28: \"suppressed-tenant requests are blocked, **modulo a brief window on\n\n  Line 54: # brief blip into a self-amplifying retry storm. 5 s gives the cache\n\n  Line 108:         # the cache write, a brief storage blip became a self-amplifying\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/routes/documents.py:\n  Line 29: # to a filesystem-safe identifier; data[\"summary\"] is embedded so other\n\n  Line 46:     # Embed source is no longer caller-chosen. Server reads data[\"summary\"]\n\n  Line 68:     Only documents written with a ``data[\"summary\"]`` (i.e. with a\n\n  Line 142:     # Resolve which string in `data` gets embedded. Only data[\"summary\"]\n\n  Line 439:      